## Mechanism Glossary (quick cues)
- **CNS stabilization:** ↑GABAergic tone / ↓excitatory glutamate → mitigates stress-provoked cortical overload → clearer thinking, fewer coordination lapses.
- **Autonomic regulation:** ↓sympathetic output (β-blockade / central sympatholytic / adaptogenic) → blunts HR/BP spikes, tremor, panic physiology.
- **HPA axis modulation:** dampens cortisol surges → reduces “crash” and next-day fatigue; may stabilize fasting glucose under stress.
- **Metabolic balance:** ↑insulin sensitivity or ↓gluconeogenesis (e.g., metformin-like effects, diet/supplement strategies) → smooths fasting glucose variability.
- **Sleep architecture support:** melatoninergic / GABAergic / orexin modulation → ↑restorative sleep → improved daytime cognition/coordination.

